title: Baroque Experience - Academy of Ancient Music 5CD TQMP
description:
This is an excellent upload thanks to John Drake from demonoid.

If you are looking for some real good Christmas music this is the one to get. 

The Baroque Experience (5-CD box set) [1991/FLAC-EAC] 

Christopher Hogwood - The Academy of Ancient Music

(This orchestra makes use of period instruments which sound a lot different than today's, resulting in a totally new listening experience, and a better one if you ask me) 

C.P.E. Bach - Symphony No. 1 
J.S. Bach - Brandenburg Concertos No. 3 & 4 
J.S. Bach - Concerto for 2 Violins & Orch. 
J.S. Bach - Orchestral Suites No. 2 & 3 
Corelli - Christmas Concerto 
Handel - Music for the Royal Fireworks 
Handel - Water Music 
Purcell - Abdelazer Suite 
Telemann - Concerto for 3 Trumpets & Orch. 
Vivaldi - The Four Seasons 
Vivaldi - Concerto for Flute and Strings No. 2 
and more... 

Sorry, only frontcover included. Tracknames in this rip however are very complete so you will know what you are listening to ;)

Please take note: When burning these discs make sure to use the .cue files!!!!

One more thing: Please help me seed this one if you like it. It deserves it.

Brought to you by TQMP. (The Quality Music Project)

In this project me and my fellow pirates share only quality items out of our CD collections in lossless FLAC and include covers, especially for those who like to burn and print and put it in a nice and shiny jewelcase. Well, you all know the drill :)
